  <description type="morphology">Plants in compact, rather dense tufts.  Stems to 6 cm.  Leaves densely imbricate and crowded, somewhat less sharply toothed than in var. commune; marginal cells of lamellae in section narrow, more shallowly grooved; peri-chaetial leaves conspicuous and ribbon-like, exceeding the foliage leaves, mostly hyaline, subentire, ending in a long, nearly smooth awn.  Capsule short-rectangular to cubic.</description>
